Anonymous Sun 28 Jul 2024 14:44:12 No.67782437 Report
Quoted By: >>67783726
>>67781086
>How to tell thread art from reposted art
It's impossible at the end of the day. But generally speaking, the more of these conditions apply, the more likely it is to be thread art
1. Literally saying "I drew this" or implying creation by the poster
2. It was drawn as a direct response to another post made recently, could have only been drawn by someone who read that particular post
3. It contains references or nods to 4chan (uncommon but it can help)
4. It was signed by a thread artist. If you don't know who the big ones are, you should probably lurk around. There's a recent list here https://desuarchive.org/trash/thread/66959538/#66964922
but it's not exhaustive and not everyone signs their work. For the rest you'll have to go by style which can be a pain in the ass if it isn't a very distinct style.
-Numerous drawfags will have conversations where every reply they make contains more of their art, some of it original. That is a strong identifier of an artist.
-Drawfags can often be seen thanking others for their compliments or placement in the OP, asking for artistic input/requests, and talking with other drawfags, etc.

There is your comprehensive guide on how to spot artists here.
